#Product rule for exponents, zero exponent 

Context("RationalFunction");

$a = random(2,9);
$b = random(2,9);

$ans = $a;


##############################################

TEXT(beginproblem());

BEGIN_PGML

Multiply and simplify. Use only positive exponents in your answer.

[` [$a] ([$b])^0 =`]  [________]{$ans} 

 
END_PGML

##############################################



BEGIN_PGML_SOLUTION
Anything raised to the zero power is 1.

[`x^0 = 1`]

That makes the expression:

[`[$a]([$b])^0 = [$a]\cdot 1 = [$a]`]

END_PGML_SOLUTION

